Israeli Stocks: Can Fite, Glycominds, Orckit Communications

-- B y   S h a r o n   W r o b e l
-- 
2011-06-05T15:11:43Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-05/israeli-stocks-glycominds-gain-and-orckit-communications-drops.html
Israel ’s TA-25 Index rose for the
first time in three days, gaining 0.2 percent to 1,230.55 at the
4:30 p.m. close in  Tel Aviv . Investors traded about 932.2
million shekels ($277 million) in shares and convertible
securities. Local markets will be closed on June 7 and June 8
for a holiday.  The following stocks rose or fell today. Symbols are in
parentheses.  Can Fite BioPharma (CFBI)  Ltd advanced the most since
May 31, increasing 0.3 percent to 0.719 shekels. The
biopharmaceutical company signed an agreement to spin off its
eye-disease division to U.S. company Denali Concrete Management
Inc.  Glycominds Ltd. (GLCM IT) climbed the most since the shares
were listed in Tel Aviv on March 1, jumping 9.1 percent to 1.622
shekels. The molecular diagnostics company reported “positive
results” in the second clinical trial using gMS-Classifier2 for
diagnosis of multiple sclerosis.  Orckit Communications Ltd. (ORCT)   dropped to the lowest
level since February 2003, declining 2.6 percent to 7.806
shekels. The maker of telecommunications equipment said it
expects to generate gross proceeds of about 28.9 million shekels
from bond offerings.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sharon Wrobel in Tel Aviv at 
 swrobel4@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
